{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I'm talking to you about"},{"time":3000,"text":"the worst form of human rights violation,"},{"time":7000,"text":"the third-largest organized crime,"},{"time":11000,"text":"a $10 billion industry."},{"time":14000,"text":"I'm talking to you about modern-day slavery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19000,"text":"I'd like to tell you the story"},{"time":21000,"text":"of these three children,"},{"time":23000,"text":"Pranitha, Shaheen and Anjali."},{"time":26000,"text":"Pranitha's mother was a woman in prostitution,"},{"time":31000,"text":"a prostituted person."},{"time":33000,"text":"She got infected with HIV,"},{"time":36000,"text":"and towards the end of her life,"},{"time":38000,"text":"when she was in the final stages of AIDS,"},{"time":41000,"text":"she could not prostitute,"},{"time":44000,"text":"so she sold four-year-old Pranitha to a broker."},{"time":51000,"text":"By the time we got the information, we reached there,"},{"time":54000,"text":"Pranitha was already raped by three men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"Shaheen's background I don't even know."},{"time":62000,"text":"We found her in a railway track,"},{"time":67000,"text":"raped by many, many men, I don't know many."},{"time":70000,"text":"But the indications of that on her body was"},{"time":73000,"text":"that her intestine was outside her body."},{"time":77000,"text":"And when we took her to the hospital"},{"time":79000,"text":"she needed 32 stitches to put back her intestine into her body."},{"time":84000,"text":"We still don't know who her parents are, who she is."},{"time":87000,"text":"All that we know that hundreds of men"},{"time":89000,"text":"had used her brutally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"Anjali's father, a drunkard,"},{"time":97000,"text":"sold his child for pornography."},{"time":101000,"text":"You're seeing here images of"},{"time":103000,"text":"three years, four-year-olds, and five-year-old children"},{"time":108000,"text":"who have been trafficked for commercial sexual exploitation."},{"time":114000,"text":"In this country, and across the globe,"},{"time":117000,"text":"hundreds and thousands of children,"},{"time":119000,"text":"as young as three, as young as four,"},{"time":122000,"text":"are sold into sexual slavery."},{"time":125000,"text":"But that's not the only purpose that human beings are sold for."},{"time":128000,"text":"They are sold in the name of adoption."},{"time":130000,"text":"They are sold in the name of organ trade."},{"time":133000,"text":"They are sold in the name of forced labor,"},{"time":135000,"text":"camel jockeying, anything, everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"I work on the issue of commercial sexual exploitation."},{"time":142000,"text":"And I tell you stories from there."},{"time":144000,"text":"My own journey to work with these children"},{"time":148000,"text":"started as a teenager."},{"time":150000,"text":"I was 15 when I was gang-raped by eight men."},{"time":156000,"text":"I don't remember the rape part of it so much"},{"time":160000,"text":"as much as the anger part of it."},{"time":166000,"text":"Yes, there were eight men who defiled me, raped me,"},{"time":169000,"text":"but that didn't go into my consciousness."},{"time":171000,"text":"I never felt like a victim, then or now."},{"time":174000,"text":"But what lingered from then till now -- I am 40 today --"},{"time":179000,"text":"is this huge outrageous anger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"Two years, I was ostracized, I was stigmatized, I was isolated,"},{"time":189000,"text":"because I was a victim."},{"time":192000,"text":"And that's what we do to all traffic survivors."},{"time":196000,"text":"We, as a society, we have PhDs"},{"time":200000,"text":"in victimizing a victim."},{"time":203000,"text":"Right from the age of 15,"},{"time":206000,"text":"when I started looking around me,"},{"time":208000,"text":"I started seeing hundreds and thousands of women and children"},{"time":212000,"text":"who are left in sexual slavery-like practices,"},{"time":216000,"text":"but have absolutely no respite,"},{"time":219000,"text":"because we don't allow them to come in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"Where does their journey begin?"},{"time":225000,"text":"Most of them come from very optionless families,"},{"time":229000,"text":"not just poor."},{"time":231000,"text":"You have even the middle class sometimes getting trafficked."},{"time":234000,"text":"I had this I.S. officer's daughter,"},{"time":237000,"text":"who is 14 years old, studying in ninth standard,"},{"time":242000,"text":"who was raped chatting with one individual,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and ran away from home because she wanted to become a heroine,"},{"time":249000,"text":"who was trafficked."},{"time":251000,"text":"I have hundreds and thousands of stories of very very well-to-do families,"},{"time":256000,"text":"and children from well-to-do families,"},{"time":258000,"text":"who are getting trafficked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"These people are deceived, forced."},{"time":264000,"text":"99.9 percent of them"},{"time":266000,"text":"resist being inducted into prostitution."},{"time":270000,"text":"Some pay the price for it."},{"time":273000,"text":"They're killed; we don't even hear about them."},{"time":277000,"text":"They are voiceless, [unclear],"},{"time":279000,"text":"nameless people."},{"time":281000,"text":"But the rest, who succumb into it,"},{"time":285000,"text":"go through everyday torture."},{"time":289000,"text":"Because the men who come to them are not men who want to make you your girlfriends,"},{"time":292000,"text":"or who want to have a family with you."},{"time":296000,"text":"These are men who buy you for an hour, for a day,"},{"time":299000,"text":"and use you, throw you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302000,"text":"Each of the girls that I have rescued --"},{"time":304000,"text":"I have rescued more than 3,200 girls --"},{"time":307000,"text":"each of them tell me one story in common ..."},{"time":310000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":312000,"text":"one story about one man, at least,"},{"time":315000,"text":"putting chili powder in her vagina,"},{"time":318000,"text":"one man taking a cigarette and burning her,"},{"time":321000,"text":"one man whipping her."},{"time":323000,"text":"We are living among those men: they're our brothers, fathers,"},{"time":326000,"text":"uncles, cousins, all around us."},{"time":329000,"text":"And we are silent about them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"We think it is easy money."},{"time":333000,"text":"We think it is shortcut."},{"time":335000,"text":"We think the person likes to do what she's doing."},{"time":339000,"text":"But the extra bonuses that she gets"},{"time":342000,"text":"is various infections, sexually transmitted infections,"},{"time":345000,"text":"HIV, AIDS, syphilis, gonorrhea, you name it,"},{"time":348000,"text":"substance abuse, drugs, everything under the sun."},{"time":352000,"text":"And one day she gives up on you and me,"},{"time":354000,"text":"because we have no options for her."},{"time":357000,"text":"And therefore she starts normalizing this exploitation."},{"time":360000,"text":"She believes, \"Yes, this is it, this is what my destiny is about.\""},{"time":365000,"text":"And this is normal, to get raped by 100 men a day."},{"time":369000,"text":"And it's abnormal to live in a shelter."},{"time":372000,"text":"It's abnormal to get rehabilitated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"It's in that context that I work."},{"time":377000,"text":"It's in that context that I rescue children."},{"time":381000,"text":"I've rescued children as young as three years,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and I've rescued women as old as 40 years."},{"time":389000,"text":"When I rescued them, one of the biggest challenges I had"},{"time":392000,"text":"was where do I begin."},{"time":396000,"text":"Because I had lots of them"},{"time":400000,"text":"who were already HIV infected."},{"time":404000,"text":"One third of the people I rescue"},{"time":406000,"text":"are HIV positive."},{"time":409000,"text":"And therefore my challenge was to"},{"time":412000,"text":"understand how can I get out"},{"time":415000,"text":"the power from this pain."},{"time":418000,"text":"And for me, I was my greatest experience."},{"time":422000,"text":"Understanding my own self,"},{"time":425000,"text":"understanding my own pain,"},{"time":427000,"text":"my own isolation,"},{"time":430000,"text":"was my greatest teacher."},{"time":432000,"text":"Because what we did with these girls"},{"time":434000,"text":"is to understand their potential."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437000,"text":"You see a girl here who is trained as a welder."},{"time":442000,"text":"She works for a very big company,"},{"time":445000,"text":"a workshop in Hyderabad,"},{"time":447000,"text":"making furnitures."},{"time":449000,"text":"She earns around 12,000 rupees."},{"time":452000,"text":"She is an illiterate girl,"},{"time":454000,"text":"trained, skilled as a welder."},{"time":457000,"text":"Why welding and why not computers?"},{"time":462000,"text":"We felt, one of the things that these girls had"},{"time":467000,"text":"is immense amount of courage."},{"time":471000,"text":"They did not have any pardas inside their body,"},{"time":475000,"text":"hijabs inside themselves;"},{"time":478000,"text":"they've crossed the barrier of it."},{"time":480000,"text":"And therefore they could fight in a male-dominated world,"},{"time":484000,"text":"very easily, and not feel very shy about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"We have trained girls as carpenters,"},{"time":491000,"text":"as masons,"},{"time":493000,"text":"as security guards, as cab drivers."},{"time":496000,"text":"And each one of them are excelling"},{"time":500000,"text":"in their chosen field,"},{"time":502000,"text":"gaining confidence, restoring dignity,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and building hopes in their own lives."},{"time":509000,"text":"These girls are also working in big construction companies"},{"time":513000,"text":"like Ram-ki construction, as masons, full-time masons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"What has been my challenge?"},{"time":523000,"text":"My challenge has not been the traffickers who beat me up."},{"time":528000,"text":"I've been beaten up more than 14 times in my life."},{"time":532000,"text":"I can't hear from my right ear."},{"time":536000,"text":"I've lost a staff of mine who was murdered"},{"time":538000,"text":"while on a rescue."},{"time":541000,"text":"My biggest challenge"},{"time":543000,"text":"is society."},{"time":545000,"text":"It's you and me."},{"time":548000,"text":"My biggest challenge is your blocks to accept these victims"},{"time":552000,"text":"as our own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555000,"text":"A very supportive friend of mine,"},{"time":558000,"text":"a well-wisher of mine,"},{"time":561000,"text":"used to give me every month, 2,000 rupees for vegetables."},{"time":565000,"text":"When her mother fell sick she said,"},{"time":567000,"text":"\"Sunitha, you have so much of contacts."},{"time":569000,"text":"Can you get somebody in my house to work,"},{"time":572000,"text":"so that she can look after my mother?\""},{"time":574000,"text":"And there is a long pause."},{"time":576000,"text":"And then she says, \"Not one of our girls.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":580000,"text":"It's very fashionable to talk about human trafficking,"},{"time":583000,"text":"in this fantastic A-C hall."},{"time":586000,"text":"It's very nice for discussion, discourse,"},{"time":590000,"text":"making films and everything."},{"time":592000,"text":"But it is not nice to bring them to our homes."},{"time":596000,"text":"It's not nice to give them employment in our factories, our companies."},{"time":602000,"text":"It's not nice for our children to study with their children."},{"time":606000,"text":"There it ends."},{"time":608000,"text":"That's my biggest challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610000,"text":"If I'm here today, I'm here not only as Sunitha Krishnan."},{"time":614000,"text":"I'm here as a voice of the victims and survivors of human trafficking."},{"time":619000,"text":"They need your compassion."},{"time":622000,"text":"They need your empathy."},{"time":624000,"text":"They need, much more than anything else,"},{"time":626000,"text":"your acceptance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"Many times when I talk to people,"},{"time":632000,"text":"I keep telling them one thing:"},{"time":634000,"text":"don't tell me hundred ways"},{"time":637000,"text":"how you cannot respond to this problem."},{"time":640000,"text":"Can you ply your mind for that one way"},{"time":643000,"text":"that you can respond to the problem?"},{"time":646000,"text":"And that's what I'm here for,"},{"time":648000,"text":"asking for your support,"},{"time":650000,"text":"demanding for your support,"},{"time":652000,"text":"requesting for your support."},{"time":654000,"text":"Can you break your culture of silence?"},{"time":657000,"text":"Can you speak to at least two persons about this story?"},{"time":661000,"text":"Tell them this story. Convince them to tell the story to another two persons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666000,"text":"I'm not asking you all to become Mahatma Gandhis"},{"time":668000,"text":"or Martin Luther Kings, or Medha Patkars,"},{"time":670000,"text":"or something like that."},{"time":672000,"text":"I'm asking you, in your limited world,"},{"time":675000,"text":"can you open your minds? Can you open your hearts?"},{"time":678000,"text":"Can you just encompass these people too?"},{"time":682000,"text":"Because they are also a part of us."},{"time":685000,"text":"They are also part of this world."},{"time":687000,"text":"I'm asking you, for these children,"},{"time":691000,"text":"whose faces you see, they're no more."},{"time":693000,"text":"They died of AIDS last year."},{"time":696000,"text":"I'm asking you to help them,"},{"time":700000,"text":"accept as human beings --"},{"time":703000,"text":"not as philanthropy, not as charity,"},{"time":706000,"text":"but as human beings who deserve all our support."},{"time":710000,"text":"I'm asking you this because no child, no human being,"},{"time":714000,"text":"deserves what these children have gone through."},{"time":717000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":719000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}